"#C45B6B","degree":11,"external":false,"id":"COVID-19","label":"COVID-19","path":"knowledge/disease/covid-19.md","subtype":"infection","type":"Disease"},{"category":"genomic","color":"#6366A8","degree":8,"external":false,"id":"IL6 (gene)","label":"IL6 (gene)","path":"knowledge/gene/il6.md","subtype":"protein_coding","type":"Gene"},{"category":"molecular","color":"#5FB0A8","degree":1,"external":false,"id":"IL-6 inhibitors","label":"IL-6 inhibitors","path":"knowledge/molecularclass/il6-inhibitors.md","subtype":"pharmacologic","type":"MolecularClass"},{"category":"molecular","color":"#2E8C84","degree":8,"external":false,"id":"Interleukin-6 (protein)","label":"Interleukin-6 (protein)","path":"knowledge/molecule/il6-protein.md","subtype":"protein","type":"Molecule"},{"category":"molecular","color":"#2E8C84","degree":10,"external":false,"id":"Tocilizumab","label":"Tocilizumab","path":"knowledge/molecule/tocilizumab.md","subtype":"antibody","type":"Molecule"},{"category":"anatomy","color":"#8FCBA6","degree":2,"external":false,"id":"SARS-CoV-2","label":"SARS-CoV-2","path":"knowledge/organism/sars-cov-2.md","subtype":"pathogen","type":"Organism"},{"category":"provenance","color":"#6B7280","degree":3,"external":false,"id":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","label":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","path":"knowledge/publication/il6-covid-review.md","subtype":"article","type":"Publication"},{"category":"genomic","color":"#AAA6DA","degree":4,"external":false,"id":"EPAS1 3' UTR","label":"EPAS1 3' UTR","path":"knowledge/sequencefeature/epas1-3prime-utr.md","subtype":"utr","type":"SequenceFeature"},{"category":"provenance","color":"#7A828E","degree":2,"external":false,"id":"RECOVERY trial","label":"RECOVERY trial","path":"knowledge/study/recovery-trial.md","subtype":"rct","type":"Study"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":1,"external":true,"id":"lung","label":"lung","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":1,"external":true,"id":"respiratory distress","label":"respiratory distress","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":1,"external":true,"id":"blood","label":"blood","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":2,"external":true,"id":"IL6 receptor","label":"IL6 receptor","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":1,"external":true,"id":"inflammatory response","label":"inflammatory response","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":1,"external":true,"id":"interleukin-6-mediated signaling","label":"interleukin-6-mediated signaling","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":1,"external":true,"id":"neutropenia","label":"neutropenia","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"},{"category":"external","color":"#B6BBC4","degree":2,"external":true,"id":"EPAS1 (gene)","label":"EPAS1 (gene)","path":null,"subtype":null,"type":"External"}]},"id":"examples","lint":{"errors":0,"infos":0,"warnings":10},"log":"# Change log\n\n## 2026-06-27\n- **Migrated the bundle to BioOKF v0.5 (node-based provenance).** Replaced every `primary_source:\n  infores:X` with a reference to a **source node** by `identifier`, and created those source nodes:\n  ingested-document sources `RECOVERY trial` (Study) and `IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)`\n  (Publication), each with a `raw_source` into `raw/`; and external-reference sources `HGNC`,\n  `UniProt` (Agents) and `Gene Ontology`, `SemMedDB`, `DrugBank`, `SIDER`, `ATC`, `MONDO`, `HPO`,\n  `Ensembl` (Datasets, `infores:` CURIE in `xref`, no `raw_source`).\n- **Dropped `provided_by`** (node-level source is now a `reported_in` edge).\n- **Made predicates forward-only:** removed `encoded_by` (the `encodes` edge lives on the gene),\n  `caused_by` (now `SARS-CoV-2 causes COVID-19`), and `treated_by` (the `treats` edge lives on the\n  drug). Added the `SARS-CoV-2` Organism node to carry the forward `causes` edge.\n- Also folded in the earlier v0.4 renames carried by this bundle: `title`+`id` → `identifier`\n  (CURIEs to `xref`); `*_kind` → `subtype`; `GenomicFeature` → `SequenceFeature` (the EPAS1 3' UTR\n  page moved to `knowledge/sequencefeature/`); added the missing `IL-6 inhibitors` MolecularClass\n  so tocilizumab's `member_of` resolves.\n\n## 2026-06-25\n- **Ingested** RECOVERY trial primary report (PMID:33933206) → created the `RECOVERY trial` Study;\n  added `treats` edge Tocilizumab→COVID-19 (RR 0.85, 95% CI 0.76–0.94, n=4116).\n- **Ingested** review of IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (PMID:32504360, PMID:32979574) → created\n  `IL6 (gene)`, `Interleukin-6 (protein)`, `COVID-19`; added `associated_with` IL6↔COVID-19 (HR 2.9).\n- **Ingested** DrugBank entry for tocilizumab (DB06273) → created `Tocilizumab`; added `binds`\n  (IL6R, Kd 2.5 nM), `regulates` (IL-6 signaling, decreased), `has_phenotype` (neutropenia),\n  `member_of` (IL-6 inhibitors).\n","name":"COVID-19 immunology (examples)","node_count":19,"pages":{"ATC":{"body":"# ATC\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:atc`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: ATC`.\n","description":"WHO Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical drug-classification system.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"ATC","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/atc.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:atc"]},"COVID-19":{"body":"# COVID-19\n\nThe disease caused by SARS-CoV-2. Its etiology is the forward `causes` edge on the\n[SARS-CoV-2](../organism/sars-cov-2.md) node (forward-only — there is no `caused_by` here).\nSevere disease features an IL-6-driven phenotype, hence the `associated_with` link to\n[IL6 (gene)](../gene/il6.md) and why [Tocilizumab](../molecule/tocilizumab.md) `treats` it.\n\n## Citations\n- [MONDO:0100096](https://monarchinitiative.org/disease/MONDO:0100096)\n","description":"Respiratory and systemic disease caused by SARS-CoV-2 infection.","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"lung","predicate":"LocatedIn","primary_source":"MONDO","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"located_in","reversed":false,"stats":{}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"respiratory distress","predicate":"HasPhenotype","primary_source":"HPO","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"has_phenotype","reversed":false,"stats":{"frequency":"frequent"}},{"agent_type":"text_mining_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"statistical_association","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL6 (gene)","predicate":"AssociatedWith","primary_source":"SemMedDB","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"associated_with","reversed":false,"stats":{"ci_lower":1.7,"ci_upper":4.9,"effect_metric":"hazard_ratio","effect_size":2.9}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","predicate":"ReportedIn","primary_source":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"reported_in","reversed":false,"stats":{}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"COVID-19","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Disease","note":null,"path":"knowledge/disease/covid-19.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Disease","subtype":"infection","synonyms":["coronavirus disease 2019","SARS-CoV-2 infection"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["MONDO:0100096","DOID:0080600","MESH:D000086382","ICD10:U07.1","UMLS:C5203670"]},"DrugBank":{"body":"# DrugBank\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:drugbank`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: DrugBank`.\n","description":"Curated drug, drug-target, and pharmacology knowledge base.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"DrugBank","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/drugbank.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:drugbank"]},"EPAS1 3' UTR":{"body":"# EPAS1 3' UTR\n\nA `SequenceFeature` (`subtype: utr`) — **not** a `Gene` and **not** a `Variant`. A UTR is a\nconstitutive *region of the reference* (Sequence Ontology `three_prime_UTR`, `SO:0000205`), so it\nfiles under `SequenceFeature`; a *deviation from the reference* would be a `Variant`. Its regulatory\n*role* is an edge, not its type.\n\n> **Class vs instance:** *this* EPAS1 3' UTR (with coordinates) is a `SequenceFeature` entity; the\n> bare notion \"a 3' UTR\" (the SO class as a label) would be a `Concept`.\n\n## Citations\n- [Altitude adaptation in Tibetans (Denisovan EPAS1)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25043035/) (Huerta-Sánchez et al. 2014)\n","description":"The 3' UTR of EPAS1 (HIF-2α) — a post-transcriptional cis-regulatory region carrying miRNA target sites and AU-rich elements that tune mRNA stability/translation.\n","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"EPAS1 (gene)","predicate":"PartOf","primary_source":"Ensembl","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"part_of","reversed":false,"stats":{}},{"agent_type":"text_mining_agent","direction":"decreased","knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"EPAS1 (gene)","predicate":"Regulates","primary_source":"SemMedDB","publications":["PMID:24759409"],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"regulates","reversed":false,"stats":{"aspect":"abundance"}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"EPAS1 3' UTR","in_taxon":"NCBITaxon:9606","node_type":"SequenceFeature","note":null,"path":"knowledge/sequencefeature/epas1-3prime-utr.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"SequenceFeature","subtype":"utr","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["SO:0000205","ENSEMBL:ENSG00000116016"]},"Ensembl":{"body":"# Ensembl\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:ensembl`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: Ensembl`.\n","description":"Genome annotation and regulatory-feature knowledge base.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"Ensembl","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/ensembl.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:ensembl"]},"Gene Ontology":{"body":"# Gene Ontology\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:go`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: Gene Ontology`.\n","description":"Gene-product function, process, and cellular-component knowledge base.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"Gene Ontology","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/gene-ontology.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":["GO"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:go"]},"HGNC":{"body":"# HGNC\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). Claims curated from HGNC name it by\n`identifier` in their `primary_source`. No `raw_source` — its authority lives in `xref`\n(`infores:hgnc`).\n","description":"HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee — authority for human gene symbols.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"HGNC","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Agent","note":null,"path":"knowledge/agent/hgnc.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Agent","subtype":"organization","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:hgnc"]},"HPO":{"body":"# HPO\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:hp`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: HPO`.\n","description":"Human Phenotype Ontology of clinical abnormalities.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"HPO","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/hpo.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":["Human Phenotype Ontology"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:hp"]},"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)":{"body":"# IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)\n\nAn **ingested-document source node** (`Publication`, `subtype: article`) anchored to `raw/` via\n`raw_source`. The IL6 gene, IL-6 protein, and COVID-19 pages each carry a `reported_in` edge to\nthis node (and source their IL-6↔COVID-19 association claims from SemMedDB).\n","description":"Review establishing IL-6 elevation as a marker of severe COVID-19 outcomes.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Publication","note":null,"path":"knowledge/publication/il6-covid-review.md","raw_source":["raw/pmid-32504360-il6-covid-review.md"],"raw_type":"Publication","subtype":"article","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["PMID:32504360","PMID:32979574"]},"IL-6 inhibitors":{"body":"# IL-6 inhibitors\n\nA `MolecularClass` (a grouping, not a single molecule). Members attach **to** it via `member_of`\n(e.g. [Tocilizumab](../molecule/tocilizumab.md) `member_of` IL-6 inhibitors) — the edge is authored\non the member, pointing here.\n","description":"Pharmacologic class of agents that block IL-6 or its receptor.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"IL-6 inhibitors","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"MolecularClass","note":null,"path":"knowledge/molecularclass/il6-inhibitors.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"MolecularClass","subtype":"pharmacologic","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["ATC:L04AC"]},"IL6 (gene)":{"body":"# IL6 (gene)\n\nThe protein-coding gene on chromosome 7p15.3 encoding **interleukin-6**. Its product\n([Interleukin-6 (protein)](../molecule/il6-protein.md)) drives the cytokine-release phenotype of\nsevere [COVID-19](../disease/covid-19.md). The gene→protein link is the forward `encodes` edge\n**here** — there is no `encoded_by` on the protein page.\n\n## Citations\n- [Elevated IL-6 and severe COVID-19](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32504360/) (PMID:32504360)\n","description":"Protein-coding gene encoding the pro-inflammatory cytokine interleukin-6.","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"Interleukin-6 (protein)","predicate":"Encodes","primary_source":"HGNC","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"encodes","reversed":false,"stats":{}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"blood","predicate":"LocatedIn","primary_source":"UniProt","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"located_in","reversed":false,"stats":{}},{"agent_type":"text_mining_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"statistical_association","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"COVID-19","predicate":"AssociatedWith","primary_source":"SemMedDB","publications":["PMID:32504360","PMID:32979574"],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"associated_with","reversed":false,"stats":{"ci_lower":1.7,"ci_upper":4.9,"effect_metric":"hazard_ratio","effect_size":2.9,"p_value":3e-6,"sample_size":1484}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","predicate":"ReportedIn","primary_source":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"reported_in","reversed":false,"stats":{}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"IL6 (gene)","in_taxon":"NCBITaxon:9606","node_type":"Gene","note":null,"path":"knowledge/gene/il6.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Gene","subtype":"protein_coding","synonyms":["IL-6","interleukin 6","BSF2","HGF","IFNB2"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["HGNC:6018","NCBIGene:3569","ENSEMBL:ENSG00000136244","OMIM:147620"]},"Interleukin-6 (protein)":{"body":"# Interleukin-6 (protein)\n\nThe secreted cytokine product of [IL6 (gene)](../gene/il6.md), and the pharmacological target of\n[Tocilizumab](tocilizumab.md). This is a **separate node from the gene** (identity, not role) —\nthey are linked by the gene's forward `encodes` edge, **not** an `encoded_by` edge here\n(predicates are forward-only).\n\n## Citations\n- [UniProt P05231](https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/P05231/entry)\n","description":"Pro-inflammatory cytokine secreted by macrophages and T cells; signals via IL6R.","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL6 receptor","predicate":"Binds","primary_source":"UniProt","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"binds","reversed":false,"stats":{}},{"agent_type":"automated_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"inflammatory response","predicate":"ParticipatesIn","primary_source":"Gene Ontology","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"participates_in","reversed":false,"stats":{"evidence_type":["ECO:0000501"]}},{"agent_type":"data_analysis_pipeline","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"statistical_association","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"COVID-19","predicate":"PredisposesTo","primary_source":"SemMedDB","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"predisposes_to","reversed":false,"stats":{"ci_lower":1.5,"ci_upper":3.3,"effect_metric":"odds_ratio","effect_size":2.2,"p_value":0.0001}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","predicate":"ReportedIn","primary_source":"IL-6 in severe COVID-19 (review)","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"reported_in","reversed":false,"stats":{}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"Interleukin-6 (protein)","in_taxon":"NCBITaxon:9606","node_type":"Molecule","note":null,"path":"knowledge/molecule/il6-protein.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Molecule","subtype":"protein","synonyms":["IL-6","interferon beta-2","BSF-2","hybridoma growth factor"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["UniProtKB:P05231","MESH:D015850","CHEMBL:CHEMBL4408","PR:000001137"]},"MONDO":{"body":"# MONDO\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:mondo`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: MONDO`.\n","description":"Monarch Disease Ontology — a unified disease vocabulary.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"MONDO","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/mondo.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:mondo"]},"RECOVERY trial":{"body":"# RECOVERY trial (tocilizumab arm)\n\nAn **ingested-document source node**: a `Study` (`subtype: rct`) distilled from the immutable file\nin `raw_source`. It evaluated [tocilizumab](../molecule/tocilizumab.md) in hospitalized\n[COVID-19](../disease/covid-19.md) patients, reducing 28-day mortality (RR 0.85, 95% CI 0.76–0.94;\nn=4116) — the evidence behind the `treats` edge on the tocilizumab page, whose `primary_source`\nnames **this node**.\n\n> A source node is provenance you can traverse to: claims point here via `primary_source` and\n> `reported_in`, and `raw_source` anchors it to the exact bytes in `raw/`.\n","description":"Large UK platform randomized controlled trial of treatments for hospitalized COVID-19.","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"Tocilizumab","predicate":"AssociatedWith","primary_source":"RECOVERY trial","publications":[],"qualifiers":{"population":"hospitalized adults with COVID-19 and hypoxia + inflammation"},"raw_predicate":"associated_with","reversed":false,"stats":{"sample_size":4116}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"RECOVERY trial","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Study","note":null,"path":"knowledge/study/recovery-trial.md","raw_source":["raw/pmid-33933206-recovery-tocilizumab.md"],"raw_type":"Study","subtype":"rct","synonyms":["RECOVERY platform trial","Randomised Evaluation of COVID-19 Therapy"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["clinicaltrials:NCT04381936","DOI:10.1016/S0140-6736(21)00676-0"]},"SARS-CoV-2":{"body":"# SARS-CoV-2\n\nThe pathogen whose forward `causes` edge points to [COVID-19](../disease/covid-19.md). Modeling\netiology as `Organism causes Disease` (not `Disease caused_by Organism`) is the forward-only rule\nin action.\n","description":"The betacoronavirus that causes COVID-19.","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"COVID-19","predicate":"Causes","primary_source":"MONDO","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"causes","reversed":false,"stats":{}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"SARS-CoV-2","in_taxon":"NCBITaxon:2697049","node_type":"Organism","note":null,"path":"knowledge/organism/sars-cov-2.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Organism","subtype":"pathogen","synonyms":["severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2","2019-nCoV"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["NCBITaxon:2697049"]},"SIDER":{"body":"# SIDER\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:sider`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: SIDER`.\n","description":"Side-effect resource: drug→adverse-event associations from labels.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"SIDER","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/sider.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:sider"]},"SemMedDB":{"body":"# SemMedDB\n\nExternal-reference **source node** (cited, not ingested). No `raw_source`; its authority\nlives in `xref` (`infores:semmeddb`). Edges sourced from it set `primary_source: SemMedDB`.\n","description":"Semantic MEDLINE Database of literature-mined subject–predicate–object triples.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"SemMedDB","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Dataset","note":null,"path":"knowledge/dataset/semmeddb.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Dataset","subtype":"knowledge_base","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:semmeddb"]},"Tocilizumab":{"body":"# Tocilizumab\n\nA humanized monoclonal antibody that **binds** the IL-6 receptor and thereby **regulates** IL-6\nsignaling downward. Shown in [RECOVERY trial](../study/recovery-trial.md) to **treat**\n[COVID-19](../disease/covid-19.md) (RR 0.85). Every `primary_source` above names a **source node**:\n`DrugBank`/`SIDER`/`ATC` are external-reference `Dataset` nodes; `RECOVERY trial` is an\ningested-document `Study` with a `raw_source`.\n\n## Citations\n- [Tocilizumab in hospital COVID-19 (RECOVERY)](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33933206/) (PMID:33933206)\n","description":"Recombinant humanized monoclonal antibody against the IL-6 receptor (IL6R).","edges":[{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL6 receptor","predicate":"Binds","primary_source":"DrugBank","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"binds","reversed":false,"stats":{"effect_metric":"Kd","effect_size":2.5}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":"decreased","knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"interleukin-6-mediated signaling","predicate":"Regulates","primary_source":"DrugBank","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"regulates","reversed":false,"stats":{"aspect":"activity"}},{"agent_type":"data_analysis_pipeline","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"statistical_association","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"COVID-19","predicate":"Treats","primary_source":"RECOVERY trial","publications":["PMID:33933206"],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"treats","reversed":false,"stats":{"ci_lower":0.76,"ci_upper":0.94,"clinical_phase":"approved","effect_metric":"relative_risk","effect_size":0.85,"sample_size":4116}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"neutropenia","predicate":"HasPhenotype","primary_source":"SIDER","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"has_phenotype","reversed":false,"stats":{"frequency":"common"}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"IL-6 inhibitors","predicate":"MemberOf","primary_source":"ATC","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"member_of","reversed":false,"stats":{}},{"agent_type":"manual_agent","direction":null,"knowledge_level":"knowledge_assertion","negated":false,"note":null,"object":"RECOVERY trial","predicate":"ReportedIn","primary_source":"RECOVERY trial","publications":[],"qualifiers":{},"raw_predicate":"reported_in","reversed":false,"stats":{}}],"extra":{},"identifier":"Tocilizumab","in_taxon":"NCBITaxon:9606","node_type":"Molecule","note":null,"path":"knowledge/molecule/tocilizumab.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Molecule","subtype":"antibody","synonyms":["atlizumab","Actemra","RoActemra"],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["DRUGBANK:DB06273","CHEMBL:CHEMBL1237022","RXNORM:612865","UNII:I031V2H011"]},"UniProt":{"body":"# UniProt\n\nExternal-reference **source node**. No `raw_source`; authority in `xref` (`infores:uniprot`).\n","description":"The Universal Protein Resource — curated protein sequence and function knowledge base.","edges":[],"extra":{},"identifier":"UniProt","in_taxon":null,"node_type":"Agent","note":null,"path":"knowledge/agent/uniprot.md","raw_source":[],"raw_type":"Agent","subtype":"organization","synonyms":[],"tags":[],"timestamp":null,"xref":["infores:uniprot"]}},"updated":"2026-06-27"}